greenmirror.commands

Class InitializationCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • greenmirror.Command
      • greenmirror.commands.InitializationCommand

  • public class InitializationCommand
extends Command
    The command to initialize the visualizer. This command is sent to the server.
    Values sent:
    variabletypedescription
    width int the width of the window
    height int the height of the window
    defaultAnimationDuration double the default time animations will take. See SetAnimationDurationCommand for details
    rotateRigidlyRelatedNodesRigidly boolean This setting determines if the "A" node of a rigid relation should rotate rigidly when the "B" node is rotated. This feature is not finished and is still buggy. When set to true, the "A" node gets the same rotation as the "B" node, resulting in its original rotation being overridden. When set to false, node A doesn't rotate which might be desirable with specific models. See the implementation of Visualizer.doPlacement(Relation) for the specific workings.
    Author:
    Karim El Assal
    See Also:
    InitializationCommandHandler, SetAnimationDurationCommand
